cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper is about attacking neural networks using an evolution algorithm, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper deals with image classification. The paper also involves optimization and search algorithms, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, since the paper discusses the vulnerability of neural networks to adversarial attacks, it could also be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
